3423:             "details1": "<ul><li>Site: Bws shorehaven</li><li>unloading 3 pallets</li></ul><p><br /></p><p></p>",
3424:             "findings1": "<ul><li>Site assessment currently indicates deliveries should be made via the rear dock, however, the rear door was locked and blocked by bins.</li><li>Driver confirmed that he has unloaded through the front enrrance in previous deliveries.</li><li>Store staff advised that deliveries are always completed through the front of the store.</li><li>Current Process requires the driver to manoeuvre pallets through outside the carpark into the front entrance of shop increasing the risk of collision with displays, stock, or customers.</li><li>There were multiple 3rd party customers entering the store during unloading, increasing exposure to pedestrian interaction.</li><li>The tail lift was used for unloading.</li><li> Store staff did not establish or assist with cone placement to control foot traffic.</li></ul>",
3425:             "attachments1": [
3426:               "/media/file?ns=6649a25a06337e51a87b77a7d83e58f522795452456649b8e019574837f8674&tip=5c6eb649b15efa7201ace283d1dc1dba42db93ca75755ab8b93d769f75e3736c",

3432:             ],
3433:             "summary1": "<ul><li>The driver was required to unload through the front store entrance as the rear dock was locked and blocked by bins.</li><li> After lowering pallets using the tail lift, the driver had to manoeuvre them through the front entrance - where there was a risk of interaction with 3rd party pedestrians and nearby vehicles.</li><li>Once inside, the driver had to navigate around product displays, increasing the risk of contact or damage to store stock.</li><li>site assessment is not consistent with unloading process which specifies rear dock delivery. Bws staff has advised me that they don't use rear dock and have always receives pallets through the front of store entrance.</li></ul><p>Reccomendation:</p><p>Review site assessment (feasibility of rear dock access and evaluate risk of unloading pallet through front entrance of store)</p>",

3553:             "details1": "<ul><li>Site - Woolworths Secret harbour </li><li>Activity - Unloading 16 pallets &amp; pick up empty pallets</li></ul><p><br /></p><p></p>",
3554:             "findings1": "<ul><li>Roadworks on the main route required a detour through a residential area.</li><li>While turning left on Atmos Road, an overhanging tree created a clearance risk of scraping trailer.</li><li>Driver slowed, checked mirrors, and reversed carefully to avoid contact, maintaining full awareness and control.</li><li>Site entry was correctly followed. Driver is aware where site assessments are on bustle app.</li><li>Reversing area tight with minimal clearance between fence line and parked vehicles (see photo).</li><li>During reverse, driver maintained slow, controlled manoeuvring with constant mirror checks.</li><li>Several cars waiting nearby, increasing potential interaction. Driver was signalling cars to stop.</li><li>Unloading involved 16 pallets into the stores receiving area.</li><li>Store established a temporary loading exclusion zone during unloading.</li><li>Loading area was clear of obstructions and hazards.</li><li>Driver positioning using EPJ was slow and controlled, away from foot and body when maneuvering. <br /></li></ul><p><br /></p>",

3564:             "summary1": "<p>On route to Woolworths Secret Harbour, we encountered unplanned roadworks and took a detour through a residential area. The route was clear from overhanging trees, however, when turning left onto Atmos Road, an overhanging tree created a clearance risk. </p><p>To avoid the tree clipping the left trailer, The driver managed the situation safely by swinging wide, checking mirrors, and adjusting the turn to avoid contact. </p><p>Upon arrival, the reversing area at the site was very tight, requiring the driver to manoeuvre close to a fence and a parked car.</p><p> Several cars passed during the manoeuvre, increasing interaction risk, but the driver remained cautious, aware, and in full control thoughout the process (he rated this maneuver a 8/10 in difficulty).</p><p>Driver used store electric epj to unload 16 pallets. Epj positioned away from body and foot. Store set up exclusion zone prior.</p><p>Upon exit, the driver consistently checked mirrors, with no overhanging branches or obstacles. The site provided wide clearance for a safe and easy departure.</p><p><br /></p>",

3637:             "findings1": "<p></p><ul><li>Accessed site via Benningfield road entering through car park.</li><li>Trolley was blocking path of exit, driver got out to remove. </li><li>No designated loading bay  truck positioned on other lane for unloading.</li><li>Dan Murphys staff established a temporary exclusion zone with cones and chains.</li><li>Ground surface uneven and slightly sloped, creating a risk for for unloading.</li><li>Driver received 12 stacks of CHEP pallets, which were blocked and contained using epj and pogo sticks.</li><li>Driver manoeuvred the EPJ within the truck while store staff used forklift to unload pallets.</li><li>Driver maintained safe positioning while using epj keeping clear of the line of fire from hands, body and foot.</li><li>Driver maintained three points of contact when climbing on the trailer deck.</li><li>Store staff was very cautious in ensuring safe transfer of pallets despite uneven ground.</li><li>Pedestrians remained clear of the exclusion zone during unloading.</li><li>During departure, the driver continuously checked mirrors and navigated carefully through the car park.</li><li>Exit route passed Dan Murphys before turning left to the main road. (Need to confirm delivery site assessments was followed).</li><li>No overhanging tree branches encountered during this run.</li></ul><p></p>",

3733:             "summary1": "<p>Jay demonstrated strong safety awareness throughout the task.  Took time to complete the job carefully in wet conditions, double-checking load positioning and performing multi test lifts. Staying away from the line of fire away from a suspended load. After completing his delivery, he did a extensive 360 walk around, ensure loads, gates were secure prior to departing.</p><p>Jay showed clear understanding of the increased risks with working in wet conditions, such as slips and reduced footing, and adjusted his approach to ensure safe unload.</p><p>When it was heavy rain, Jay did not rush the job, he still took his time to re-strap the load, close the underdeck gates, take photos of product. He displays a strong commitment to his job and is diligent in doing the task correctly and safely. </p><p><br /></p><p><br /></p>",

3843:             "summary1": "<p></p><ul><li>Driver displayed continuous observation skills whilst reversing a semi truck into a minimal space unloading area</li><li>Driver parked on level ground</li><li>Driver chocked wheels and ensured the area was clear  </li><li>Driver communicated well with site employees that were still operating around the area  </li><li>Driver used correctly all PPE that is required to fulfil the task (Long Sleeve High Vis, Helmet, Face Shield, Earmuffs, Gloves, Steel cap boots )</li><li>Driver ensured that the power cord has sufficient length to reach plug</li><li>Knowledge of correct refilling procedure and sequence to safely complete task / refill</li><li>Using tools provided to undo nuts and caps on vessels ( Pouring water over connections to melt ice )</li><li>Packing up of all hoses and equipment once task completed</li><li>Final check to ensure all taps and valves have been closed and all is secured before leaving site </li></ul><p></p>",
3844:             "summary2": "<p></p><li>Driver displayed continuous observation skills whilst reversing a semi truck into a minimal space unloading     area </li><li>Driver parked on level ground</li><li>Driver chocked wheels and ensured the area was clear  </li><li>Driver communicated well with site employees that were still operating near the area  </li><li>Driver correctly used all PPE provided to fulfil the task (Long Sleeve High Vis, Helmet, Face  Shield, Earmuffs, Gloves, Steel cap boots )</li><li>Driver ensured that the power cord has sufficient length to reach power point</li><li>Knowledge of correct refilling procedure and sequence of valves to be Opened / Closed  </li><li>Using correct tools to undo nuts and caps on vessels and from the Tanker ( pour water over connections to melt ice )</li><li>Packing up of all hoses and equipment once task had been completed</li><li>Final recheck to ensure all taps and valves have been closed and all is secured before leaving site</li><li>********************* PLS NOTE *******************</li><li>Whilst the driver was refilling the Liquid Oxygen Vessel onsite, one of the Wenco PTY employees was walking past the truck then all of a sudden instead of continuing along his path around the truck, he turned left and walked under the middle of the tanker .  The driver trainer ( Jason Mathews ) yelled out to the employee but the employee carried on through. The driver trainer then walked around the truck to address the employee but the employee had already jumped in his vehicle and was driving down the road .</li><p></p>",
3845:             "summary3": "<p></p><li>Driver displayed continuous observation skills whilst reversing semi truck into a minimal space unloading area </li><li>Driver chocked wheels and ensured the area was clear  </li><li>Driver communicated well with other employees that were still operating around the area  </li><li>Driver used all PPE correctly that is required to commence the task (Long Sleeve High Vis, Helmet, Face Shield, Earmuffs, Gloves, Steel cap boots )</li><li>Driver ensured that the power cord has sufficient length to reach plug</li><li>Knowledge of correct refilling procedure and sequence of valves to be Opened / Closed  </li><li>Using correct tools to undo nuts and caps on vessels ( Pouring water over connections to melt ice )</li><li>Packing up of all hoses and equipment once task had been completed</li><li>Final check to ensure all taps and valves have been closed and all is secured before leaving site</li><p></p>",

154:         if has_raw_json:

20:             msg['To'] = "user@noggin-system.local"

23:             {insp_type} Export
24:             ----------------------------------------
25:             ID: {insp_id}
26:             Export Date: {datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}
27:             The original attachments for this record are included in the attached ZIP file.
28:             """
29:             msg.set_content(body_content)
30:             zip_buffer = io.BytesIO()
31:             with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_buffer, 'w', zipfile.ZIP_DEFLATED) as zip_file:
32:                 for att in attachments:
33:                     file_path = att.get('file_path')
34:                     filename = att.get('filename')
35:                     if file_path and os.path.exists(file_path):
36:                         try:
37:                             zip_file.write(file_path, arcname=filename)
38:                         except Exception as zip_err:

47:                 subtype='zip',

49:             )
50:             eml_buffer = io.BytesIO(msg.as_bytes())
51:             eml_buffer.seek(0)

356:         if retry_count >= self.max_retries:
357:             return datetime.now() + timedelta(days=365 * 10)
358:         delay_minutes: float = self.base_delay_minutes * (self.backoff_multiplier ** retry_count)
359:         max_delay_minutes: float = self.max_delay_hours * 60
360:         delay_minutes = min(delay_minutes, max_delay_minutes)
361:         return datetime.now() + timedelta(minutes=delay_minutes)

363:         return retry_count < self.max_retries
364: class ProgressTracker:
365:     def __init__(self, total_count: int) -> None:
366:         self.total_count: int = total_count
367:         self.processed_count: int = 0
368:         self.start_time: float = time.perf_counter()
369:         self.last_log_time: float = self.start_time
370:         self.log_interval: int = 10
371:     def increment(self) -> None:
372:         self.processed_count += 1
373:     def should_log_progress(self) -> bool:
374:         current_time = time.perf_counter()
375:         if current_time - self.last_log_time >= self.log_interval:
376:             self.last_log_time = current_time
377:             return True
378:         return False
379:     def get_progress_stats(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:
380:         elapsed: float = time.perf_counter() - self.start_time
381:         if self.processed_count > 0:
382:             rate: float = self.processed_count / elapsed
383:             remaining: int = self.total_count - self.processed_count
384:             eta_seconds: float = remaining / rate if rate > 0 else 0
385:         else:
386:             rate = 0
387:             eta_seconds = 0
388:         return {
389:             'processed': self.processed_count,
390:             'total': self.total_count,
391:             'elapsed_seconds': elapsed,
392:             'rate_per_second': rate,
393:             'eta_seconds': eta_seconds,
394:             'percent_complete': (self.processed_count / self.total_count * 100) if self.total_count > 0 else 0
395:         }
396:     def log_progress(self) -> None:
397:         stats = self.get_progress_stats()
398:         eta_minutes: float = stats['eta_seconds'] / 60
399:         elapsed_minutes: float = stats['elapsed_seconds'] / 60
400:         logger.info(
401:             f"Progress: {stats['processed']}/{stats['total']} "
402:             f"({stats['percent_complete']:.1f}%) - "
403:             f"{stats['rate_per_second']:.2f} TIPs/sec - "
404:             f"Elapsed: {elapsed_minutes:.1f}m - "
405:             f"ETA: {eta_minutes:.1f}m"
406:         )
407:     def log_shutdown_summary(self, reason: str = "complete") -> None:
408:         stats = self.get_progress_stats()
409:         elapsed_minutes: float = stats['elapsed_seconds'] / 60
410:         logger.info("=" * 60)
411:         logger.info(f"PROCESSING {reason.upper()}")
412:         logger.info(f"Processed: {stats['processed']}/{stats['total']} TIPs")
413:         logger.info(f"Duration: {elapsed_minutes:.1f} minutes")
414:         logger.info(f"Average rate: {stats['rate_per_second']:.2f} TIPs/sec")
415:         logger.info("=" * 60)

239:     Returns list of dicts with keys: tip, object_type, inspection_id, inspection_date
240:     """
241:     tips = []
242:     with open(csv_path, 'r', newline='', encoding='utf-8-sig') as f:
243:         reader = csv.reader(f)
244:         headers = [h.strip() for h in next(reader)]
245:         # First column is always nogginId (TIP), regardless of header name
246:         tip_index = 0
247:         id_index = find_column_index(headers, api_id_field)
248:         date_index = find_column_index(headers, 'date')
249:         if id_index == -1:
250:             logger.warning(f"API ID field '{api_id_field}' not found in headers")
251:             id_index = None
252:         if date_index == -1:
253:             logger.warning("Date column not found in headers")
254:             date_index = None
255:         for row_num, row in enumerate(reader, start=2):
256:             if not row or not row[tip_index].strip():
257:                 continue
258:             tip_value = row[tip_index].strip()
259:             inspection_id = None
260:             if id_index is not None and len(row) > id_index:
261:                 inspection_id = row[id_index].strip() or None
262:             inspection_date = None
263:             if date_index is not None and len(row) > date_index:
264:                 date_str = row[date_index].strip()
265:                 if date_str:
266:                     inspection_date = parse_date(date_str)
267:             tips.append({
268:                 'tip': tip_value,
269:                 'object_type': object_type_meta['full_name'],
270:                 'abbreviation': object_type_meta['abbreviation'],
271:                 'inspection_id': inspection_id,
272:                 'inspection_date': inspection_date,
273:                 'row_number': row_num
274:             })
275:     logger.info(f"Extracted {len(tips)} TIPs from {csv_path.name}")
276:     return tips
277: def parse_date(date_str: str) -> Optional[str]:
278:     """
279:     Parse date string to ISO format (YYYY-MM-DD)
280:     Handles multiple formats commonly found in Noggin exports
281:     """
282:     formats = [
283:         '%d-%b-%y',      # 16-Jun-25
284:         '%d-%b-%Y',      # 16-Jun-2025
285:         '%d/%m/%Y',      # 16/06/2025
286:         '%d/%m/%y',      # 16/06/25
287:         '%Y-%m-%d',      # 2025-06-16
288:         '%d-%m-%Y',      # 16-06-2025
289:         '%d-%m-%y',      # 16-06-25
290:     ]
291:     for fmt in formats:
292:         try:
293:             parsed = datetime.strptime(date_str, fmt)
294:             return parsed.strftime('%Y-%m-%d')
295:         except ValueError:
296:             continue
297:     logger.debug(f"Could not parse date: {date_str}")
298:     return None
299: def check_existing_tips(db_manager: DatabaseConnectionManager,
300:                         tips: List[str]) -> set:
301:     """Check which TIPs already exist in database"""
302:     if not tips:
303:         return set()
304:     placeholders = ', '.join(['%s'] * len(tips))
305:     query = f"SELECT tip FROM noggin_data WHERE tip IN ({placeholders})"
306:     results = db_manager.execute_query_dict(query, tuple(tips))
307:     return {row['tip'] for row in results}
308: def insert_tips_to_database(db_manager: DatabaseConnectionManager,
309:                             tips_data: List[Dict[str, Any]],
310:                             source_file: str,
311:                             warning_logger: logging.Logger) -> Dict[str, int]:
312:     """
313:     Insert new TIPs into database with pending status
314:     Uses individual inserts with transaction for rollback on failure.
315:     Skips existing TIPs and logs to warning file.
316:     Falls back to basic insert if new columns don't exist yet.
317:     Returns dict with counts: inserted, duplicates, errors
318:     """
319:     if not tips_data:
320:         return {'inserted': 0, 'duplicates': 0, 'errors': 0}
321:     tip_values = [t['tip'] for t in tips_data]
322:     existing_tips = check_existing_tips(db_manager, tip_values)
323:     inserted = 0
324:     duplicates = 0
325:     errors = 0
326:     # Try full insert first, fall back to basic if columns missing
327:     insert_query_full = """
328:         INSERT INTO noggin_data (
329:             tip, object_type, processing_status,
330:             expected_inspection_id, expected_inspection_date,
331:             csv_imported_at, source_filename
332:         )
333:         VALUES (%s, %s, 'pending', %s, %s, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, %s)
334:     """
335:     insert_query_basic = """
336:         INSERT INTO noggin_data (
337:             tip, object_type, processing_status, csv_imported_at
338:         )
339:         VALUES (%s, %s, 'pending', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
340:     """
341:     use_full_insert = True
342:     for tip_data in tips_data:
343:         tip_value = tip_data['tip']
344:         if tip_value in existing_tips:
345:             duplicates += 1
346:             warning_logger.warning(
347:                 f"DUPLICATE TIP skipped | "
348:                 f"tip={tip_value[:16]}... | "
349:                 f"object_type={tip_data['abbreviation']} | "
350:                 f"inspection_id={tip_data['inspection_id']} | "
351:                 f"source={source_file}"
352:             )
353:             continue
354:         try:
355:             if use_full_insert:
356:                 db_manager.execute_update(
357:                     insert_query_full,
358:                     (
359:                         tip_value,
360:                         tip_data['object_type'],
361:                         tip_data['inspection_id'],
362:                         tip_data['inspection_date'],
363:                         source_file
364:                     )
365:                 )
366:             else:
367:                 db_manager.execute_update(
368:                     insert_query_basic,
369:                     (tip_value, tip_data['object_type'])
370:                 )
371:             inserted += 1
372:             logger.debug(f"Inserted TIP: {tip_value[:16]}... ({tip_data['abbreviation']})")
373:         except Exception as e:
374:             error_str = str(e).lower()
375:             # Check if error is due to missing columns
376:             if 'column' in error_str and ('expected_inspection' in error_str or 'source_filename' in error_str):
377:                 logger.warning("New columns not found, falling back to basic insert")
378:                 use_full_insert = False
379:                 try:
380:                     db_manager.execute_update(
381:                         insert_query_basic,
382:                         (tip_value, tip_data['object_type'])
383:                     )
384:                     inserted += 1
385:                     logger.debug(f"Inserted TIP (basic): {tip_value[:16]}... ({tip_data['abbreviation']})")
386:                 except Exception as e2:
387:                     errors += 1
388:                     logger.error(f"Failed to insert TIP {tip_value[:16]}...: {e2}")
389:             else:
390:                 errors += 1
391:                 logger.error(f"Failed to insert TIP {tip_value[:16]}...: {e}")
392:         except Exception as e:
393:             errors += 1
394:             logger.error(f"Failed to insert TIP {tip_value[:16]}...: {e}")
395:     logger.info(
396:         f"Database insert complete: {inserted} inserted, "
397:         f"{duplicates} duplicates, {errors} errors"
398:     )
399:     return {'inserted': inserted, 'duplicates': duplicates, 'errors': errors}
400: def write_audit_csv(tips_data: List[Dict[str, Any]], audit_dir: Path,

418: def archive_file(source_path: Path, processed_dir: Path,
419:                  object_type_abbrev: str) -> Path:
420:     """
421:     Move file to processed directory with timestamp prefix
422:     Filename format: {ABBREV}_{YYYY-MM-DD}_{HHMMSS}_{original_uuid}.csv
423:     """
424:     timestamp = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')
425:     original_stem = source_path.stem
426:     if original_stem.startswith('exported-file-'):
427:         uuid_part = original_stem.replace('exported-file-', '')
428:     else:
429:         uuid_part = original_stem
430:     archive_filename = f"{object_type_abbrev}_{timestamp}_{uuid_part}.csv"
431:     archive_path = processed_dir / archive_filename
432:     shutil.move(str(source_path), str(archive_path))
433:     logger.debug(f"Archived: {source_path.name} -> {archive_filename}")
434:     return archive_path
435: def quarantine_file(source_path: Path, quarantine_dir: Path,
436:                     reason: str, error_logger: logging.Logger) -> Path:
437:     """Move unidentified file to quarantine directory"""
438:     timestamp = datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S')

440:     quarantine_path = quarantine_dir / quarantine_filename
441:     shutil.move(str(source_path), str(quarantine_path))
442:     error_logger.error(
443:         f"FILE QUARANTINED | "
444:         f"original={source_path.name} | "
445:         f"reason={reason} | "
446:         f"quarantine_path={quarantine_path}"
447:     )
448:     logger.warning(f"File quarantined: {source_path.name} - {reason}")
449:     return quarantine_path
450: def delete_remote_file(sftp: paramiko.SFTPClient, filename: str,
451:                        files_to_delete: List[str]) -> None:
452:     """Add file to deletion queue (actual deletion happens after all processing)"""
453:     files_to_delete.append(filename)
454:     logger.debug(f"Queued for deletion: {filename}")
455: def execute_remote_deletions(sftp: paramiko.SFTPClient,
456:                              files_to_delete: List[str]) -> int:
457:     """Delete all queued files from SFTP server"""
458:     deleted = 0
459:     for filename in files_to_delete:
460:         try:
461:             sftp.remove(filename)
462:             deleted += 1
463:             logger.debug(f"Deleted from SFTP: {filename}")
464:         except Exception as e:
465:             logger.error(f"Failed to delete {filename} from SFTP: {e}")
466:     if deleted > 0:
467:         logger.info(f"Deleted {deleted} files from SFTP server")
468:     return deleted
469: def process_single_file(
470:     sftp: paramiko.SFTPClient,
471:     remote_filename: str,
472:     paths: Dict[str, Path],
473:     db_manager: Optional[DatabaseConnectionManager],
474:     sftp_logger: SFTPLoggerManager,
475:     config: ConfigParser,
476:     files_to_delete: List[str]
477: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
478:     result = {
479:         'filename': remote_filename,
480:         'status': 'unknown',
481:         'object_type': None,
482:         'tips_found': 0,
483:         'inserted': 0,
484:         'duplicates': 0,
485:         'errors': 0
486:     }
487:     local_file = None
488:     try:
489:         local_file = download_file(sftp, remote_filename, paths['incoming'])
490:         try:
491:             api_id_field, object_meta = detect_object_type(local_file)
492:             result['object_type'] = object_meta['abbreviation']
493:         except ObjectTypeDetectionError as e:
494:             quarantine_file(local_file, paths['quarantine'], str(e),
495:                            sftp_logger.error_logger)
496:             result['status'] = 'quarantined'
497:             return result
498:         tips_data = extract_tips_from_csv(local_file, api_id_field, object_meta)
499:         result['tips_found'] = len(tips_data)
500:         if not tips_data:
501:             logger.warning(f"No TIPs found in {remote_filename}")
502:             result['status'] = 'empty'
503:         write_audit = config.getboolean('processing', 'write_audit_csv', fallback=True)
504:         if write_audit and tips_data:
505:             write_audit_csv(tips_data, paths['tip_audit'], remote_filename)
506:         insert_to_db = config.getboolean('processing', 'insert_to_database', fallback=True)
507:         if insert_to_db and db_manager and tips_data:
508:             db_result = insert_tips_to_database(
509:                 db_manager, tips_data, remote_filename,
510:                 sftp_logger.warning_logger
511:             )
512:             result.update(db_result)
513:         archive_file(local_file, paths['processed'], object_meta['abbreviation'])
514:         local_file = None
515:         delete_after = config.getboolean('processing', 'delete_from_sftp_after_archive',
516:                                          fallback=True)
517:         if delete_after:
518:             delete_remote_file(sftp, remote_filename, files_to_delete)
519:         result['status'] = 'success'
520:     except Exception as e:
521:         logger.error(f"Error processing {remote_filename}: {e}", exc_info=True)
522:         sftp_logger.error_logger.error(
523:             f"PROCESSING FAILED | file={remote_filename} | error={e}"
524:         )
525:         result['status'] = 'error'
526:         result['errors'] = 1
527:         if local_file and local_file.exists():
528:             quarantine_file(local_file, paths['quarantine'],
529:                            f"Processing error: {e}", sftp_logger.error_logger)
530:     return result
531: def run_sftp_download(
532:     sftp_config_path: str = 'config/sftp_config.ini',
533:     base_config: Optional[ConfigLoader] = None,
534:     db_manager: Optional[DatabaseConnectionManager] = None
535: ) -> Dict[str, Any]:
536:     """
537:     Main entry point for SFTP download process
538:     Can be called standalone or from continuous processor.
539:     Args:
540:         sftp_config_path: Path to SFTP configuration file
541:         base_config: Optional existing ConfigLoader (for logging paths)
542:         db_manager: Optional existing database connection
543:     Returns:
544:         Summary dict with processing statistics
545:     """
546:     summary = {
547:         'start_time': datetime.now().isoformat(),
548:         'files_processed': 0,
549:         'total_tips_found': 0,
550:         'total_inserted': 0,
551:         'total_duplicates': 0,
552:         'total_errors': 0,
553:         'files_quarantined': 0,
554:         'files_deleted_from_sftp': 0,
555:         'status': 'unknown'
556:     }
557:     ssh_client = None
558:     sftp_client = None
559:     own_db_manager = False
560:     try:
561:         sftp_config = load_sftp_config(sftp_config_path)
562:         paths = create_directories(sftp_config)
563:         if base_config:
564:             log_path = Path(base_config.get('paths', 'base_log_path'))
565:         else:
566:             log_path = Path('/mnt/data/noggin/log')
567:         sftp_logger = SFTPLoggerManager(sftp_config, log_path)
568:         sftp_logger.configure_sftp_loggers()
569:         if db_manager is None:
570:             if base_config is None:
571:                 base_config = ConfigLoader(
572:                     'config/base_config.ini',
573:                     'config/load_compliance_check_driver_loader_config.ini'
574:                 )
575:             db_manager = DatabaseConnectionManager(base_config)
576:             own_db_manager = True
577:         ssh_client, sftp_client = connect_sftp(sftp_config)
578:         remote_dir = sftp_config.get('sftp', 'remote_directory')
579:         csv_files = list_csv_files(sftp_client, remote_dir)
580:         if not csv_files:
581:             logger.info("No CSV files found on SFTP server")
582:             summary['status'] = 'no_files'
583:             return summary
584:         files_to_delete: List[str] = []
585:         for filename, mtime in csv_files:
586:             logger.info(f"Processing: {filename}")
587:             result = process_single_file(
588:                 sftp_client, filename, paths, db_manager,
589:                 sftp_logger, sftp_config, files_to_delete
590:             )
591:             summary['files_processed'] += 1
592:             summary['total_tips_found'] += result.get('tips_found', 0)
593:             summary['total_inserted'] += result.get('inserted', 0)
594:             summary['total_duplicates'] += result.get('duplicates', 0)
595:             summary['total_errors'] += result.get('errors', 0)
596:             if result['status'] == 'quarantined':
597:                 summary['files_quarantined'] += 1
598:         deleted_count = execute_remote_deletions(sftp_client, files_to_delete)
599:         summary['files_deleted_from_sftp'] = deleted_count
600:         summary['status'] = 'success'
601:         summary['end_time'] = datetime.now().isoformat()
602:         logger.info("=" * 60)
603:         logger.info("SFTP DOWNLOAD SUMMARY")
604:         logger.info("=" * 60)
605:         logger.info(f"Files processed:     {summary['files_processed']}")
606:         logger.info(f"TIPs found:          {summary['total_tips_found']}")
607:         logger.info(f"TIPs inserted:       {summary['total_inserted']}")
608:         logger.info(f"Duplicates skipped:  {summary['total_duplicates']}")
609:         logger.info(f"Errors:              {summary['total_errors']}")
610:         logger.info(f"Files quarantined:   {summary['files_quarantined']}")
611:         logger.info(f"Deleted from SFTP:   {summary['files_deleted_from_sftp']}")
612:         logger.info("=" * 60)
613:         return summary
614:     except SFTPConnectionError as e:
615:         logger.error(f"SFTP connection error: {e}")
616:         summary['status'] = 'connection_error'
617:         summary['error'] = str(e)
618:         return summary
619:     except Exception as e:
620:         logger.error(f"SFTP download failed: {e}", exc_info=True)
621:         summary['status'] = 'error'
622:         summary['error'] = str(e)
623:         return summary
624:     finally:
625:         if sftp_client:
626:             sftp_client.close()
627:         if ssh_client:
628:             ssh_client.close()
629:         if own_db_manager and db_manager:
630:             db_manager.close_all()
631:         logger.info("SFTP connection closed")
632: def main() -> int:
633:     try:
634:         base_config = ConfigLoader(
635:             'config/base_config.ini',
636:             'config/load_compliance_check_driver_loader_config.ini'
637:         )
638:         logger_manager = LoggerManager(base_config, script_name='sftp_download_tips')
639:         logger_manager.configure_application_logger()
640:         logger.info("=" * 80)
641:         logger.info("SFTP TIP DOWNLOADER - STANDALONE MODE")
642:         logger.info("=" * 80)
643:         result = run_sftp_download(base_config=base_config)
644:         if result['status'] == 'success':
645:             return 0
646:         else:
647:             return 1
648:     except KeyboardInterrupt:
649:         logger.warning("Download interrupted by user")
650:         return 1
651:     except Exception as e:
652:         logger.error(f"Fatal error: {e}", exc_info=True)
653:         return 1
654: if __name__ == "__main__":
655:     sys.exit(main())

 53: class HashResolver:
 54:     HASH_PATTERN = re.compile(r'^[a-fA-F0-9]{64}$')
 55:     def __init__(self, db_manager: 'DatabaseConnectionManager') -> None:
 56:         self.db_manager = db_manager
 57:         self._cache: Dict[str, Optional[str]] = {}
 58:         self._cache_hits: int = 0
 59:         self._cache_misses: int = 0
 60:     def is_hash(self, value: str) -> bool:
 61:         if not value or not isinstance(value, str):
 62:             return False
 63:         return bool(self.HASH_PATTERN.match(value.strip()))
 64:     def resolve(self, hash_value: str) -> Optional[str]:
 65:         if not hash_value:
 66:             return None
 67:         hash_value = hash_value.strip()
 68:         if hash_value in self._cache:
 69:             self._cache_hits += 1
 70:             return self._cache[hash_value]
 71:         self._cache_misses += 1
 72:         try:
 73:             rows = self.db_manager.execute_query_dict(
 74:                 "SELECT resolved_value FROM hash_lookup WHERE tip_hash = %s",
 75:                 (hash_value,)
 76:             )
 77:             if rows:
 78:                 resolved = rows[0]['resolved_value']
 79:                 self._cache[hash_value] = resolved
 80:                 return resolved
 81:             else:
 82:                 self._cache[hash_value] = None
 83:                 return None
 84:         except Exception as e:
 85:             logger.warning(f"Hash lookup failed for {hash_value[:16]}...: {e}")
 86:             return None
 87:     def resolve_or_passthrough(self, value: str) -> Tuple[Optional[str], Optional[str]]:
 88:         """
 89:         Resolve a value if it's a hash, otherwise pass through.
 90:         Returns:
 91:             Tuple of (resolved_value, hash_value)
 92:             - If input is a hash: (resolved_text or None, original_hash)
 93:             - If input is text: (original_text, None)
 94:         """
 95:         if not value:
 96:             return (None, None)
 97:         value = str(value).strip()
 98:         if self.is_hash(value):
 99:             resolved = self.resolve(value)
100:             return (resolved, value)
101:         else:
102:             return (value, None)
103:     def get_cache_stats(self) -> Dict[str, int]:
104:         """Return cache statistics"""
105:         return {
106:             'cache_size': len(self._cache),
107:             'cache_hits': self._cache_hits,
108:             'cache_misses': self._cache_misses
109:         }
110:     def clear_cache(self) -> None:
111:         """Clear the resolution cache"""
112:         self._cache.clear()
113:         self._cache_hits = 0
114:         self._cache_misses = 0

116:     """
117:     Loads preview field configurations from INI files.
118:     Each object type's INI file should have a [csv_import] section defining
119:     which fields to extract for web search interface.
120:     """
121:     HASH_COLUMN_MAP: Dict[str, str] = {
122:         'team': 'team_hash',
123:         'vehicle': 'vehicle_hash',
124:         'trailer': 'trailer_hash',
125:         'trailer2': 'trailer2_hash',
126:         'trailer3': 'trailer3_hash',
127:         'department': 'department_hash',
128:     }
129:     def __init__(self, config_dir: Path) -> None:
130:         self.config_dir = config_dir
131:         self._configs: Dict[str, ObjectTypePreviewConfig] = {}
132:     def load_config(self, abbreviation: str) -> ObjectTypePreviewConfig:
133:         """Load preview field config for an object type."""
134:         if abbreviation in self._configs:
135:             return self._configs[abbreviation]
136:         object_config = OBJECT_TYPES.get(abbreviation)
137:         if not object_config:
138:             raise CSVImportError(f"Unknown object type: {abbreviation}")
139:         config_file = self.config_dir / object_config.config_file
140:         preview_fields: List[PreviewFieldMapping] = []
141:         if config_file.exists():
142:             parser = ConfigParser()
143:             parser.read(config_file)
144:             if parser.has_section('csv_import'):
145:                 for csv_col, db_col in parser.items('csv_import'):
146:                     is_hash = db_col in self.HASH_COLUMN_MAP
147:                     hash_col = self.HASH_COLUMN_MAP.get(db_col) if is_hash else None
148:                     preview_fields.append(PreviewFieldMapping(
149:                         csv_column=csv_col,
150:                         db_column=db_col,
151:                         is_hash_field=is_hash,
152:                         hash_db_column=hash_col
153:                     ))
154:                 logger.debug(f"Loaded {len(preview_fields)} preview fields from {config_file.name}")
155:             else:
156:                 logger.warning(f"INI file {config_file.name} missing [csv_import] section. Only basic ID/Date will be mapped.")
157:         else:
158:             logger.warning(f"Config file not found: {config_file}. Only basic ID/Date will be mapped.")
159:         result = ObjectTypePreviewConfig(
160:             abbreviation=abbreviation,
161:             id_column=object_config.id_column,
162:             date_column=object_config.date_column,
163:             preview_fields=preview_fields
164:         )
165:         self._configs[abbreviation] = result
166:         return result

168:     """Parses CSV rows and extracts preview fields with hash resolution."""
169:     def __init__(self, headers: List[str], preview_config: ObjectTypePreviewConfig,
170:                  hash_resolver: HashResolver) -> None:
171:         self.headers = headers
172:         self.preview_config = preview_config
173:         self.hash_resolver = hash_resolver

175:         self._build_column_index_map()
176:     def _build_column_index_map(self) -> None:
177:         """Build mapping of field names to column indices"""
178:         for mapping in self.preview_config.preview_fields:
179:             idx = find_column_index(self.headers, mapping.csv_column)
180:             if idx >= 0:
181:                 self._column_indices[mapping.csv_column] = idx
182:             else:
183:                 logger.debug(f"Column '{mapping.csv_column}' not found in CSV headers")
184:         idx = find_column_index(self.headers, self.preview_config.id_column)
185:         if idx >= 0:
186:             self._column_indices[self.preview_config.id_column] = idx
187:         idx = find_column_index(self.headers, self.preview_config.date_column)
188:         if idx >= 0:
189:             self._column_indices[self.preview_config.date_column] = idx
190:     def parse_row(self, row: List[str]) -> Dict[str, Any]:
191:         row = [val.strip() for val in row]
192:         result: Dict[str, Any] = {}
193:         tip = row[0].strip() if row else ''
194:         if not tip:
195:             return {}
196:         result['tip'] = tip
197:         result['object_type'] = self.preview_config.abbreviation
198:         date_col = self.preview_config.date_column
199:         if date_col in self._column_indices:
200:             idx = self._column_indices[date_col]
201:             if idx < len(row):
202:                 raw_date = row[idx].strip()
203:                 result['expected_inspection_date'] = self._parse_date(raw_date)
204:         id_col = self.preview_config.id_column
205:         if id_col in self._column_indices:
206:             idx = self._column_indices[id_col]
207:             if idx < len(row):
208:                 raw_id = row[idx].strip()
209:                 if raw_id:
210:                     result['expected_inspection_id'] = raw_id
211:         for mapping in self.preview_config.preview_fields:
212:             if mapping.csv_column not in self._column_indices:
213:                 continue
214:             idx = self._column_indices[mapping.csv_column]
215:             if idx >= len(row):
216:                 continue
217:             raw_value = row[idx].strip()
218:             if not raw_value:
219:                 continue
220:             if mapping.is_hash_field:
221:                 resolved, hash_val = self.hash_resolver.resolve_or_passthrough(raw_value)
222:                 if resolved:
223:                     result[mapping.db_column] = resolved
224:                 if hash_val and mapping.hash_db_column:
225:                     result[mapping.hash_db_column] = hash_val
226:             else:
227:                 result[mapping.db_column] = raw_value
228:         return result
229:     def _parse_date(self, date_str: str) -> Optional[datetime]:
230:         if not date_str:
231:             return None
232:         formats = [
233:             '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S.%fZ',
234:             '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ',
235:             '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S',
236:             '%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S',
237:             '%Y-%m-%d',
238:             '%d-%b-%y',
239:             '%d-%B-%Y',
240:             '%d/%m/%Y',
241:             '%m/%d/%Y',
242:             '%d %b %Y',
243:             '%d %b %y',
244:             '%d-%b-%Y',
245:             '%d-%b-%y',
246:         ]
247:         for fmt in formats:
248:             try:
249:                 return datetime.strptime(date_str, fmt)
250:             except ValueError:
251:                 continue
252:         logger.debug(f"Could not parse date: {date_str}")
253:         return None
254: class BatchInserter:
255:     """
256:     Handles batch insertion of records into the database.
257:     Uses INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING to efficiently skip duplicates.
258:     """
259:     def __init__(self, db_manager: 'DatabaseConnectionManager', batch_size: int = 100) -> None:
260:         self.db_manager = db_manager
261:         self.batch_size = batch_size
262:         self._pending: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []
263:         self._inserted_count: int = 0
264:         self._duplicate_count: int = 0
265:     def add(self, record: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:
266:         """Add a record to the batch"""
267:         if record and record.get('tip'):
268:             self._pending.append(record)
269:         if len(self._pending) >= self.batch_size:
270:             self.flush()
271:     def flush(self) -> Tuple[int, int]:
272:         """Flush pending records to database."""
273:         if not self._pending:
274:             return (0, 0)
275:         batch_inserted = 0
276:         batch_duplicates = 0
277:         tips = [r['tip'] for r in self._pending]
278:         existing_tips = self._get_existing_tips(tips)
279:         new_records = [r for r in self._pending if r['tip'] not in existing_tips]
280:         batch_duplicates = len(self._pending) - len(new_records)
281:         if new_records:
282:             batch_inserted = self._insert_batch(new_records)
283:         self._inserted_count += batch_inserted
284:         self._duplicate_count += batch_duplicates
285:         self._pending.clear()
286:         return (batch_inserted, batch_duplicates)
287:     def _get_existing_tips(self, tips: List[str]) -> set:
288:         """Check which TIPs already exist in database"""
289:         if not tips:
290:             return set()
291:         placeholders = ','.join(['%s'] * len(tips))
292:         query = f"SELECT tip FROM noggin_data WHERE tip IN ({placeholders})"
293:         try:
294:             rows = self.db_manager.execute_query_dict(query, tuple(tips))
295:             return {row['tip'] for row in rows}
296:         except Exception as e:
297:             logger.error(f"Error checking existing TIPs: {e}")
298:             return set()
299:     def _insert_batch(self, records: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> int:
300:         """Insert a batch of records"""
301:         if not records:
302:             return 0
303:         current_time = datetime.now()
304:         columns = [
305:             'tip',
306:             'object_type',
307:             'processing_status',
308:             'csv_imported_at',
309:             'created_at',
310:             'updated_at',
311:             'source_filename',
312:             'expected_inspection_id',
313:             'expected_inspection_date'
314:         ]
315:         placeholders = ', '.join(['%s'] * len(columns))
316:         insert_sql = f"""
317:             INSERT INTO noggin_data ({', '.join(columns)})
318:             VALUES ({placeholders})
319:             ON CONFLICT (tip) DO NOTHING
320:         """
321:         inserted = 0
322:         for record in records:
323:             values = (
324:                 record.get('tip'),
325:                 record.get('object_type'),
326:                 'csv_imported',
327:                 current_time,
328:                 current_time,
329:                 current_time,
330:                 record.get('source_filename'),
331:                 record.get('expected_inspection_id'),
332:                 record.get('expected_inspection_date')
333:             )
334:             try:
335:                 result = self.db_manager.execute_update(insert_sql, values)
336:                 if result > 0:
337:                     inserted += 1
338:             except Exception as e:
339:                 logger.error(f"Insert failed for TIP {record.get('tip', 'unknown')[:16]}...: {e}")
340:         return inserted
341:     def get_stats(self) -> Dict[str, int]:
342:         """Get insertion statistics"""
343:         return {
344:             'inserted': self._inserted_count,
345:             'duplicates': self._duplicate_count,
346:             'pending': len(self._pending)
347:         }

359:         self._updated_count: int = 0

363:     def add(self, record: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:

366:             self._pending.append(record)

368:             self.flush()
369:     def flush(self) -> None:

371:         if not self._pending:
372:             return
373:         tips = [r['tip'] for r in self._pending]

375:         # {tip: {processing_status, expected_inspection_id, expected_inspection_date}}

379:             tip = record['tip']

382:                 self._insert_new_record(record)
383:                 continue
384:             db_record = existing_map[tip]

386:                 self._skipped_complete += 1

388:             # Determine which fields need updating (only if DB value is NULL)
389:             updates = {}
390:             csv_id = record.get('expected_inspection_id')

393:                 updates['expected_inspection_id'] = csv_id
394:             if csv_date and db_record['expected_inspection_date'] is None:
395:                 updates['expected_inspection_date'] = csv_date

397:                 self._skipped_no_change += 1
398:                 continue

395: @auth.login_required
396: def service_status():
397:     def get_service_info(service_name: str, log_lines: int = 50) -> dict:
398:         try:
399:             status_result = subprocess.run(
400:                 ['systemctl', 'is-active', service_name],
401:                 capture_output=True,
402:                 text=True
403:             )
404:             is_active = status_result.stdout.strip() == 'active'
405:             log_result = subprocess.run(
406:                 ['journalctl', '-u', service_name, '-n', str(log_lines), '--no-pager'],
407:                 capture_output=True,
408:                 text=True
409:             )
410:             logs = log_result.stdout or log_result.stderr or 'No logs available'
411:             detail_result = subprocess.run(
412:                 ['systemctl', 'show', service_name, '--property=ActiveState,SubState,MainPID,MemoryCurrent'],
413:                 capture_output=True,
414:                 text=True
415:             )
416:             details = {}
417:             for line in detail_result.stdout.strip().split('\n'):
418:                 if '=' in line:
419:                     key, value = line.split('=', 1)
420:                     details[key] = value
421:             return {
422:                 'name': service_name,
423:                 'active': is_active,
424:                 'state': details.get('ActiveState', 'unknown'),
425:                 'substate': details.get('SubState', 'unknown'),
426:                 'pid': details.get('MainPID', 'N/A'),
427:                 'memory': details.get('MemoryCurrent', 'N/A'),
428:                 'logs': logs
429:             }
430:         except Exception as e:
431:             logger.warning(f"NOBBY SAYS: Could not get status for {service_name}: {e}")
432:             return {
433:                 'name': service_name,
434:                 'active': False,
435:                 'state': 'error',
436:                 'substate': str(e),
437:                 'pid': 'N/A',
438:                 'memory': 'N/A',
439:                 'logs': f'NOBBY SAYS: Error fetching logs: {e}'
440:             }
441:     try:
442:         web_service = get_service_info('noggin-web')
443:         processor_service = get_service_info('noggin-processor')
444:         active_tab = request.args.get('tab', 'web')
445:         return render_template(
446:             'service_status.html',
447:             web_service=web_service,
448:             processor_service=processor_service,
449:             active_tab=active_tab
450:         )
451:     except Exception as e:
452:         logger.error(f"Status check failed: {e}")
453:         return "Status check failed", 500
